HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 717
By McCalmon
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Page High School
football team, TSSAA Division I, Class 5A state
champion.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Page High School football team achieved an extraordinary level of
success during the 2025 season, winning the coveted Tennessee Secondary School Athletic
Association (TSSAA) Division I, Class 5A State Football Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Page Patriots vanquished every opponent for an undefeated season on
their way to the BlueCross Bowl championship game on December 5, 2025, at Finley Stadium
in Chattanooga, where they beat Sevier County High School in a hard-fought battle in the title
matchup; and
WHEREAS, on their path to the championship game for the fifth consecutive year, the
Patriots defeated Hendersonville 62-0, Kirkwood 24-7, Beech 31-21, Centennial 43-21, and
Sevier County 21-14 to secure the right to hoist the iconic gold football trophy; and
WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Patriots exhibited
each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the members of the 2025 Class 5A State Champion football team are
Knight Wilson, Colt Brown, Elijah Pimentel, Ryder Casillas, Sean Cunningham, Peyton
Dickerson, Cayden Aukerman, Drew Rempel, Isaac Otey, Cameron Kruse, Cal Wiebush, Mack
Lee, Colin Mulick, Taylen Cisneros, Flynn Steele, Quincy Finley, Tyson Cobb, Grady Cason,
