Levi Cissell, Olin Hapgood, Cohen Grissom, Colton Zuhlke, Eli Bell, James Pierre, Paxton
Walters, Grant Dickens, Everett Humphrey, Jacob Smith, Liam Strother, Wyatt Heck-McGinnis,
Jackson Nestor, Tyson Robbins, Asher Lorenzen, Grant White, Wrigley Braden, Braden
Magowan, Harrison Griffin, Sam Goerzen, Hattan Cozart, Riley Crandall, Liam Perry, Grant
Pittman, Will Platz, Grahm Johnson, Nolan Belew, Graham Griffin, Cooper Mueller, Elijah
Kincade, Porter Whitehead, Jonathan Baba, Caleb Coffman, Joven Hacker, Maddox Morgan,
Kingston Wells, Dabbs Matthews, Daniel Callahan, Nicholas Brady, Cash Couleas, Raymond
Giles, Levi Winn, Jesse Kitts, Ryland Wright, Evan Van Utrecht, Austin Belsky, Jacob Rathbone,
Emmanuel Johnson, Jordan Curll, Chance Gregg, Brandon Beckett, Bennett Kauffman, Sloan
Bass, Preston Ashmore, Evrett Tutt, Frankie Patruno, Rhett Adkins, John Rider, Thomas
Dowling, Bennett Klump, Owen Yarbrough, Ryan Narancich, Joseph Guerra, and Connor
Sullivan; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 Page Patriots enjoyed the services of an outstanding coaching
staff, namely Head Coach Charles Rathbone and assistant coaches Curt Anes, Jay Emmons,
Jason Hoath, Stephen King, Jerry McGlown, John Nestor, Miller Polk, Travis Sheppard, Sean
Temple, Scott Wells, Caedon Williams, Shane Williams, and James Wolff, who instilled in these
exceptional young men a commitment to excellence in all that they do and encouraged
maximum effort on the football field; and
WHEREAS, the football players of Page High School epitomize all that is good in today's
student athletes, as they have achieved the highest level of success on the field while showing
the highest degree of character both on and off the gridiron; they inspired their fellow students
and united the entire community during their triumphant run through the 2025 season; and
WHEREAS, the dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of young
men not only made possible a championship football season but also surely bode well for their
success in every future endeavor; and
- 2 - 010523

WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the football players of
Page High School for serving as exemplars of the high quality of the youth of Tennessee; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the players, coaching staff, team support staff,
administrators, cheerleaders, and fans of the Page High School football team on winning the
2025 TSSAA Division I, Class 5A State Football Championship.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
